cafes.name: Cat Show Cat Café
cafes.address: Inside The Market Building, 730 Boardwalk Ave, Bozeman, MT 59718, USA

text.text:
Spent an hour here with my daughter. We made a reservation online ahead of time and paid in the store. If you’re like me, it helps to know what to expect. We did not have any trouble with the check-in. The one staff person available was very friendly, even though there’s clearly lots happening with the café and the store.

She escorted us upstairs to a very large room where there were 8 cats, lots of cat toys, beautiful plants, a restroom, tables and chairs (many types of seating). We washed our hands and then my daughter sat down to wait for the cats to come to her. Some did and some didn’t, but they’re obviously well taken care of.

The treat machine needs 2 quarters on EACH side ($1 total) to purchase a little plastic ball with treats inside. I’m mentioning this because even though the woman clearly explained it and there were written directions, my daughter (almost 12) got confused. Each ball had enough treats to give one to each cat. Bob was treat-aggressive (for a cat).

We had a lovely hour. I was anxious in not knowing what to expect (and then being worried that we broke the treat machine), but I will be able to relax next time because now I know how the whole thing works.

My daughter loves cats, but we cannot have them, so this was a great experience for her and she’s looking forward to returning. This is a truly lovely idea and the shop looked super cute. We will have to come with enough time to browse next time.

I had a great time meeting all the cats! They are all super friendly and love pets and treats. Some of the cats were napping and didn't approach, but they loved it when I went over to say hello. I'll definitely be back!
The cats Eddie, David, Bob, Stella, Mildew, Mossy, Captain Jack Sparrow, and Alexis are all so sweet and they loved being held and pet and even cuddled up with for a quick snooze.

cafes.name: Cateye Cafe
cafes.address: 23 N Tracy Ave, Bozeman, MT 59715, USA

text.text: Really enjoyed our visit for breakfast on a Saturday morning.  We ordered a breakfast special which was a huckleberry strawberry cream cheese stuffed croissant French toast , and it was absolutely delicious.  We also ordered the biscuits and gravy which was so tasty too!  The atmosphere is lovely and the staff was efficient and friendly.  Great spot.

Fun menu and good food.
We had the Popeye and the Cowgirl. Both were good, although the banana bread French toast was a little disappointing as it did not have as much flavor as expected.
Go early as they get busy.

What a great place! I just happened to drive by and I loved the sign and the building, so I had  to go in for breakfast. What a treat - a funky little cafe with great food and friendly service. I had eggs with bacon and Swiss on a biscuit - The Witch. Thick, crunchy bacon and excellent biscuit. I'll definitely be coming back!
